<task id="WCWE-001" project="UI Create Wizard Enhancements R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Fix theme cascade — remove OS prefers-color-scheme fallback</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>frontend, fluent-ui, shared-library, theme</tags>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Fix resolveCodePageTheme() and getEffectiveDarkMode() in the shared theme utilities to remove the
    OS prefers-color-scheme media query as the final fallback (level 4). When no explicit Spaarke theme
    is set, default to light mode. Also remove the prefers-color-scheme media query change listener
    from setupCodePageThemeListener and setupThemeListener so OS-level dark mode toggles have zero
    effect on Spaarke UI.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior frontend developer with expertise in Fluent UI v9, React, and Dataverse Code Pages</role>

  <goal>
    Code Pages and shared components render in light mode by default. Dark mode activates only when
    the Spaarke theme menu explicitly selects dark. OS dark mode preference has no effect on any
    Spaarke UI surface.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">All UI must use Fluent UI v9 design tokens; theme is controlled by the Spaarke theme system, not the OS.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Theme utilities live in @spaarke/ui-components shared library; changes propagate to all consumers.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/utils/codePageTheme.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/utils/themeStorage.ts</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      UAT feedback (E-17) identified that Code Pages incorrectly inherit OS dark mode via the
      prefers-color-scheme media query fallback. Users on OS dark mode see dark UI even though they
      never set Spaarke to dark mode. The theme cascade should be: (1) URL param, (2) localStorage,
      (3) Dataverse user setting — and if none found, default to light.
    </background>
    <dependencies />
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Audit theme cascade">Read codePageTheme.ts and themeStorage.ts; map the current 4-level fallback chain and identify all references to prefers-color-scheme.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Remove OS fallback from resolvers">In resolveCodePageTheme(), remove the level-4 prefers-color-scheme check; return light theme as default. Do the same in getEffectiveDarkMode().</step>
    <step order="3" name="Remove media query listeners">In setupCodePageThemeListener and setupThemeListener, remove window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)') event listeners.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Update type signatures if needed">Ensure ThemeSource or similar enums no longer include an 'os' or 'system' variant if one exists.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify build">Run npm build for Spaarke.UI.Components to confirm no compile errors.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Search for other OS fallback references">Grep the codebase for prefers-color-scheme to ensure no other files still use it for theme decisions.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/utils/codePageTheme.ts</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/utils/themeStorage.ts</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Code Pages render in light mode by default when no Spaarke theme is explicitly set.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dark mode activates only when user selects dark via the Spaarke theme menu.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">OS dark mode toggle has no effect on Spaarke UI rendering.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">grep -r "prefers-color-scheme" src/client/shared/ returns zero results related to theme fallback logic.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Shared library builds without errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
